  "title": "Freelance Drama Teacher",
  "description": "<p><br /><strong>Job Scope & Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>1. Flexible Teaching Deployment</strong></p><ul><li><p>Conduct drama programmes for a diverse range of age groups from 18 months to 15 years.</p></li><li><p>Assignments may include <strong>either or both</strong> of the following, based on schedule and suitability:</p><ul><li><p>External programmes in Preschools, Primary, and Secondary schools.</p></li><li><p>Weekend classes on-site at <strong>ACT 3 Drama Academy</strong>.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>2. Curriculum Delivery</strong></p><ul><li><p>Deliver lessons strictly according to the syllabus, lesson plans and teaching methods prescribed by <strong>ACT 3 Drama Academy</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Use only the teaching materials and aids approved by the Academy.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements & Qualifications</h3><p><strong>Experience & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Existing Drama Pedagogy:</strong> Candidates must possess a foundation in drama teaching skills. We are looking for practitioners who understand the basics of drama education; you will then be trained specifically on the <strong>ACT 3 Drama Academy</strong> methodology.</p></li><li><p><strong>Classroom Management:</strong> Proven ability to manage a class effectively, maintaining discipline and order while keeping the energy positive.</p></li><li><p><strong>Engagement:</strong> The ability to engage children. You must genuinely enjoy working with children of various ages.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Professional Attributes</strong></p><p><p>Punctual and reliable with a high standard of work ethics.</p></p><p>Flexible and adaptable to different school environments and age groups from time to time.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
